      "content": "There is no right answer to such a heavy question, especially when the foundation of your life feels hollowed out. However, identity is not a single static object but rather a collection of moments, people, and values that continue to exist even after a specific project fails. When the work no longer defines you, it becomes an opportunity to rediscover who you are without that one lens, rather than forcing yourself to live in a version of yourself that no longer fits.",
